Inputs

1\Quiz 1 mark
2\Quiz 2 mark
3\Quiz 3 mark
4\Choice (Y/N)

Process

User enters three quiz marks.
Program calculates the average.
Program checks if average is 50 or above.
Program displays Pass or Fail.
Program asks whether to continue.

Outputs

Average mark
Pass or Fail
Program Ended
Pseudocode

Start

Set choice = "y"

While choice == "y"
    Input quiz1
    Input quiz2
    Input quiz3

    average = (quiz1 + quiz2 + quiz3) / 3

    If average >= 50
        Display Pass
    Else
        Display Fail

    Input choice
End While

Display Program Ended
End
